      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>April 29 article about Deputy Mayor Joseph J Lhota misstated composition of 'inability committee' that would decide on succession should mayor be unable to serve out term</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Saturday about Deputy Mayor Joseph J. Lhota of New York misstated the composition of an ''inability committee'' that would decide on succession should a mayor be unable to serve out the term. The committee comprises the corporation counsel, the comptroller, the speaker of the City Council, a deputy mayor designated by the mayor, and the borough president with the longest consecutive service. The committee does not include the public advocate.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
